# [IANABIS](../wg/ianabis.html)

## Summary
The IANABIS working group met at IETF 126 in Vienna to discuss updates to the core guidelines for IANA registries. The primary focus of the meeting was addressing challenges with the "Specification Required" registry policy, including the definition of "permanent and readily available" specifications and the issue of squatting on common terms. The group also discussed key updates to `draft-ietf-ianabis-rfc7120bis` (Early IANA Code Point Allocation) and `draft-ietf-ianabis-rfc8126bis` (Guidelines for Writing an IANA Considerations Section in RFCs), focusing heavily on preventing numeric code point collisions and defining appropriate registry governance structures.

