### 3. Early IANA Code Point Allocation (`draft-ietf-ianabis-rfc7120bis`)
* **Presenter:** Amanda Baber (IANA)
* **Slides:** [IANA IANABIS 126](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-ianabis-iana-ianabis-126-02)
* **Discussion Summary:**
  * Amanda Baber summarized changes since the last meeting, including extending early allocations from 1 year to 2 years, requiring expert approval prior to IETF Last Call, and adding an early allocation procedure for SDOs in "Specification Required" registries. 
  * FCFS and Expert Review "early" allocations (which are permanent) were moved to a separate section to clear up confusion.
  * **Discussion:**
    * **Eliot Lear** raised a recurring concern regarding early allocations to Internet Drafts: if subsequent draft versions change the protocol behavior, there is no standardized tooling or mechanism to track whether the assigned code point is still valid or if incompatibilities have been introduced. Amanda Baber requested specific tooling proposals to be sent to the mailing list for further discussion.

